Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #grill{} to high or #oven{} or #toaster oven{} to 400 degrees. Pick leaves from @sage{1/4%ounce}; discard stems. Mince leaves until you have 1 1/2 tsp. Peel @shallot{1}, then grate into a #medium bowl{}.

> Alternatively, finely mince shallot.

Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}, sage, @dried thyme{1/2%tsp}, and @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} (we sent more thyme and panko) to bowl with shallot. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} (we used 1/2 tsp kosher salt). Mix with your hands until just combined, then form into two patties slightly wider than the buns.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add turkey patties and cook until no longer pink in center, ~{5-6%minutes} per side.

> If grilling, grill patties on cleaned and oiled grates over direct heat.

Meanwhile, stir together @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and @cranberry jam{1%tablespoon} (we sent more) in a #small bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Split @potato buns{2} and place in oven (or toaster oven) until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> If grilling, toast buns on grill over indirect heat.

Toss together @mixed greens{4%ounce}, @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, @pecans{1%ounce}, @balsamic vinegar{1%tablespoon} (we sent more), and a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread cranberry mayo on buns. Fill each with a turkey patty and a small handful of salad. Serve with remaining salad on the side.